== Horns and Antlers

- **True Horns** (Family Bovidae): Hollow sheaths of keratinized epidermis around a core of bone. Not shed, not branched, grow continuously, found in both sexes.
- **Antlers** (Family Cervidae): Branched and composed of solid bone when mature.
  - Develop beneath vascular soft skin called **velvet**.
  - Shed after the breeding season.
  - Usually only in males (except caribou).
- **Rhinoceros Horn**: Hairlike keratinized filaments cemented together, not attached to the skull.

