= Mammalian Populations

- Populations fluctuate due to density-independent (climate, catastrophes) and density-dependent (crowding, competition) factors.
- **Cycles of Abundance**:
  - **Lemmings**: Mass migrations and population crashes every 3-4 years.
  - **Snowshoe Hares**: 10-year cycles correlated with lynx (predator) populations. Crashes may be due to "shock disease" (endocrine imbalance) from crowding.

